    dc:creator "Lagos, Doris M.; Puttler, Benjamin; Voegtlin, David J.; Giordano, Rosanna" ;
    dc:title "Aphis mizzou Lagos and Puttler, sp.n." ;
    trt:definesTaxonConcept <http://taxon-concept.plazi.org/id/Animalia/Aphis_mizzou_Puttler_2012> ;
    trt:publishedIn <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.210015> ;
    a trt:Treatment .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.210015>
    bibo:endPage "92" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "81" ;
    bibo:volume "3478" ;
    dc:creator "Lagos, Doris M.; Puttler, Benjamin; Voegtlin, David J.; Giordano, Rosanna" ;
    dc:date "2012" ;
    dc:title "A new species of Aphis (Hemiptera: Aphididae) in Missouri on St. John’s Wort, Hypericum kalmianum, and re-description of Aphis hyperici Monell" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.210016>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.210023>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.210017>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.210018>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.210019> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.210016>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Apterous vivipara of A. mizzou (INHS: 511,101 collection number). (A) body, (B) eight tergite abdominal, (C) first marginal tubercle and hind coxa, (D) sub-genital plate, (E) cauda, (F) ultimate rostral segment, (G) siphunculus, (H) seventh marginal tubercle." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/210016/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.210023>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Colonies of aphids on Hypericum spp. A. A. mizzou n. sp. on H. kalmianum, B. A. hyperici on H. kalmianum (photos by C. J. Starbuck), C. A. hypericiphaga on H. perforatum (photo by H. Kim)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/210023/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.210017>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Alate vivipara of A. mizzou. (A) body, (B) hind tibia, (C) third antennal segment, (D) ultimate rostral segment, (E) siphunculus, (F) seventh marginal tubercle, (G) cauda, (H) first marginal tubercle and hind coxa, (I) sub-genital plate, (J) eight tergite abdominal." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/210017/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.210018>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Neighbor-joining tree (K 2 P) distances using the nuclear gene EF 1 - α. Species names are followed by the collection locality (U. S. A): IA (Iowa), IL (Illinois), and MO (Missouri) and number of haplotypes." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/210018/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.210019>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Neighbor- joining tree (K 2 P) distances using the combined data set of COI and EF 1 - α genes." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/210019/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

